emy of Sciences and Humanities (elected in 2013), and regular member of the Academia Europaea (since 2010).   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aGlobalizationxHistory. 0aLiterature and globalization. 0aLiterature and transnationalism. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 4aComparative Literature. 4aCultural History. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur und Raum. 4aLiterature and Space. 4aTransArea Studies. 4aTransArea-Forschung. 4aVergleichende Literaturwissenschaft. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh1 aPerson, Mark W.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104777950 cprintz978311047773340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110480177423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110480177.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DKUb2016